13. Kaduna State Government has secured the convictions of 311 violators of lockdown order out of the 373 people that were apprehended in two days. The Commissioner for Justice and Attorney General, Mrs Aisha Dikko, disclosed this in a statement on Wednesday in Kaduna. She said the convictions were made by the eight mobile courts that were set up last week to try residents, who flouted the restriction order and other COVID-19 precautionary measures. The Attorney